<div class="guide-wrapper">
  <div class="guide-container">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="guide-header">
      <h1>👩‍👧 New Moms - Read This</h1>
      <p>Your Complete Guide to Baby Care & Product Selection</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Welcome Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>💝 Welcome to Motherhood!</h2>
      <p>Congratulations on your new arrival! This guide is designed by experienced mothers and pediatric experts to help you navigate the world of baby care products. We understand that choosing the right products for your baby can be overwhelming, so we've compiled essential information to make your journey easier.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Choosing Products Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>🛍️ How to Choose Baby Products</h2>

      <h3>Safety First</h3>
      <p>Always look for products that meet safety certifications and standards. In India, check for ISI (Indian Standards Institute) marks. International brands should have CE marks (European Conformity).</p>

      <h3>Quality Over Price</h3>
      <p>Baby products are an investment in your child's health. Don't compromise on quality to save a few rupees. Higher quality often means:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Better durability and longer use</li>
        <li>Safer materials (no harmful chemicals)</li>
        <li>Better for sensitive skin</li>
        <li>Easier to clean and maintain</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Read Reviews</h3>
      <p>Check reviews from other mothers who have used the product. Real experiences from parents are invaluable for making decisions.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Dos Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>✅ DOs for Baby Care</h2>

      <div class="do-list">
        <h4>Feeding</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Breastfeed for at least 6 months (WHO recommendation)</li>
          <li>Sterilize bottles and pacifiers before first use and regularly after</li>
          <li>Use warm (not hot) water for mixing formula</li>
          <li>Hold baby upright while feeding to prevent choking</li>
          <li>Burp your baby after feeding to release gas</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="do-list">
        <h4>Sleep & Safety</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Place baby on back for sleeping</li>
          <li>Use a firm, flat surface (crib or bassinet)</li>
          <li>Keep pillows and blankets away from baby's face</li>
          <li>Maintain room temperature between 68-72°F</li>
          <li>Use a sleep sack instead of loose blankets</li>
          <li>Room-share without bed-sharing for at least 6 months</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="do-list">
        <h4>Hygiene & Health</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Wash hands before handling baby</li>
          <li>Change diapers every 2-3 hours</li>
          <li>Use mild, fragrance-free baby soap and shampoo</li>
          <li>Bathe baby 2-3 times a week (more frequent bathing dries skin)</li>
          <li>Keep umbilical cord area clean and dry</li>
          <li>Follow vaccination schedule strictly</li>
          <li>Trim baby's nails regularly with safety scissors</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="do-list">
        <h4>Clothing & Temperature</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Dress baby in one more layer than you wear</li>
          <li>Choose breathable, cotton fabrics</li>
          <li>Avoid overdressing which can cause heat stress</li>
          <li>Check baby's neck and back to feel if they're warm/cold</li>
          <li>Use mittens to prevent baby from scratching face</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DON'Ts Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>❌ DON'Ts for Baby Care</h2>

      <div class="dont-list">
        <h4>Feeding Mistakes</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Never use honey for babies under 1 year (risk of botulism)</li>
          <li>Don't give cow's milk as main drink before 1 year</li>
          <li>Don't introduce solids before 6 months</li>
          <li>Don't leave baby unattended with bottle</li>
          <li>Don't reuse formula that baby has started drinking</li>
          <li>Don't feed baby hot food directly from microwave</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dont-list">
        <h4>Sleep Safety Mistakes</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Never sleep with baby on couch or armchair</li>
          <li>Don't use pillows, blankets, or bumpers in crib</li>
          <li>Don't co-sleep if you're under influence of drugs/alcohol</li>
          <li>Don't use baby sleep positioners</li>
          <li>Don't use wedges to keep baby propped</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dont-list">
        <h4>Health & Safety Mistakes</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Don't use talc powder (high aspiration risk)</li>
          <li>Don't apply oils/creams without patch test</li>
          <li>Don't leave baby unattended on changing tables</li>
          <li>Don't use adult products on baby skin</li>
          <li>Don't ignore signs of illness (fever, rash, unusual crying)</li>
          <li>Don't expose baby to secondhand smoke</li>
          <li>Don't use baby walkers (injury risk)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="dont-list">
        <h4>Environment Mistakes</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Don't use heavily scented products near baby</li>
          <li>Don't expose baby to extreme temperatures</li>
          <li>Don't leave baby in direct sunlight without protection</li>
          <li>Don't forget to wear seat belt while driving with baby</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Precautions Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>⚠️ Important Precautions</h2>

      <h3>When to Call Doctor Immediately</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Temperature above 100.4°F (38°C) for babies under 3 months</li>
        <li>Difficulty breathing or gasping</li>
        <li>Unconsciousness or unresponsiveness</li>
        <li>Severe rash or unusual discoloration</li>
        <li>Projectile vomiting or continuous vomiting</li>
        <li>No bowel movement for 3+ days</li>
        <li>Signs of dehydration (dry lips, fewer wet diapers)</li>
        <li>Persistent crying or excessive irritability</li>
        <li>Yellow discoloration of skin (jaundice)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Product Storage & Expiry</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Always check expiry dates before purchasing</li>
        <li>Store medicines in cool, dry places</li>
        <li>Keep baby products away from direct sunlight</li>
        <li>Never use open/damaged product containers</li>
        <li>Follow storage instructions on product labels</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Allergies & Sensitivity</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Always do patch test with new products (24 hours)</li>
        <li>Watch for signs of allergic reaction (rash, redness, swelling)</li>
        <li>Start with hypoallergenic products for sensitive skin</li>
        <li>Introduce one new product at a time</li>
        <li>Keep ingredients list for allergy tracking</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Monthly Development Guide -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>📅 Baby Milestones & Care by Month</h2>

      <h3>First 3 Months</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Feeding, sleeping, bonding</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Establish feeding routine</li>
        <li>Understand different types of baby cries</li>
        <li>Practice gentle handling and support</li>
        <li>Begin tummy time for 1-2 minutes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3-6 Months</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Development, interaction, introduction to solids</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Increase tummy time gradually</li>
        <li>Talk, sing, and play with baby regularly</li>
        <li>Watch for readiness signs for solids (around 6 months)</li>
        <li>Introduce toys appropriate for age</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>6-12 Months</h3>
      <p><strong>Focus:</strong> Solids introduction, mobility, exploration</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Start with single-ingredient purees</li>
        <li>Gradually introduce more foods (wait 3-5 days between new foods)</li>
        <li>Ensure safe crawling environment</li>
        <li>Baby-proof your home</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Product Recommendations -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>🛒 Essential Baby Products Every Mom Needs</h2>

      <h3>Feeding Essentials</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>BPA-free bottles and nipples</li>
        <li>Bottle sterilizer</li>
        <li>High chair (6+ months)</li>
        <li>Feeding bibs (leak-proof)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Sleeping Essentials</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Safe crib or bassinet</li>
        <li>Firm mattress with fitted sheet</li>
        <li>Sleep sacks (instead of blankets)</li>
        <li>Waterproof mattress protector</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Hygiene Essentials</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Gentle baby soap and shampoo</li>
        <li>Soft washcloths</li>
        <li>Baby nail clippers with safety guard</li>
        <li>Diaper rash cream</li>
        <li>Wet wipes or cotton balls</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Health & Safety</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Digital thermometer</li>
        <li>Baby monitor with video</li>
        <li>First aid kit for babies</li>
        <li>Humidifier for dry weather</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Self-Care Section -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>💪 Mama's Self-Care is Important Too</h2>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <strong>💝 Remember:</strong> You cannot pour from an empty cup. Taking care of yourself is not selfish—it's essential for being a good mother. Get enough sleep, eat well, stay hydrated, and ask for help when you need it.
      </div>

      <h3>Managing Postpartum Challenges</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Postpartum depression is real—seek help if you feel it</li>
        <li>Breastfeeding pain is treatable—consult lactation expert</li>
        <li>Sleep deprivation is temporary—ask family for help</li>
        <li>Mood swings are normal—be kind to yourself</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Building Your Support Network</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Connect with other new mothers</li>
        <li>Join parenting groups (online or offline)</li>
        <li>Don't hesitate to ask family and friends for help</li>
        <li>Regular check-ins with your doctor</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Final Message -->
    <div class="guide-section">
      <h2>🌟 Final Words</h2>
      <p>There's no such thing as a "perfect" mother. You're going to make mistakes, and that's okay. What matters is that you're trying your best, loving your baby, and learning as you go. Every mother has been where you are, feeling overwhelmed and uncertain. Trust your instincts, ask for help when needed, and remember that you're doing an amazing job!</p>
      <p style="margin-top: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #FF69B4;">You've got this, mama! 💕</p>
    </div>

    <a href="/" class="back-btn">← Back to Shopping</a>
  </div>
</div>

